ww.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_question_mark.gif" align=absmiddle>  What do you look for in your story lines?</span><hr size=1> I was just thinking...What do I think makes a great story line and I figured I'd ask all of you what your thoughts are...<br>
<br>
I think a great story line involves some of (But not limited to) the following...<br>
<br>
Revenge, Love, Love Triangles, Betrayal, Mystery, Discovery<br>
<br>
I've been working on a storyline for a possible &quot;comic&quot; but I'd need some talented people to do the other side of it....<br>
<br>
Ok, here's an example...lets look at something most of us are familiar with &quot;SPIDERMAN&quot;....Starts off as just a dork, aquires mysterious powers, but is torn between his identity, his family and his first true love. The whole time he must keep things hidden from ones he loves, in fear that they will find out who he really is. While the girl he loves goes off with other guys etc......Throw in some bad guys for his alter ego to contend with and the story goes on auto-pilot for a LONG TIME....<br>
<br>
See what I mean?<br>
<br>
SO, what makes a good story line to YOU?! (Oh and would anyone be interested in my original, even though NOTHING is original, ideas?)  THANKS!<br>
<br>
