<br>
I see that everyone agrees on most points....That's pretty much what I was looking for!!! It seems that most people like a good involved story where the characters GROW and LEARN as the story progresses.<br>
<br>
Plot twists are GREAT when used properly.  But, as stated, more than 2 or 3 and it just turns into a friggin' circus.<br>
<br>
I like stories that BUILD....start with a character and observe them for a while and just when you have an understanding of that character THROW them into a situation where they have to CHANGE (Emotionally, physically, spiritually etc.) or die. OR, they are faced with something that they can't understand and you get to watch them figure it out.<br>
<br>
I'm Building a base of characters that have been brought together by chance (or is it fate?!) They all rely on one another for survival, friendship etc... But the main character is what I've described above - Just an ordinary person (Or so it seems) who discovers something about himself that drives him to find the truth with his new found friends.<br>
